span> Beqa</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">בֶּקַע</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(beqa‘)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:22\">GEN 24:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:26\">EXO 38:26</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:26\">EXO 38:26</a> a <em>beqa‘</em> is defined as half a shekel. In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:22\">GEN 24:22</a> it is the weight of a gold nose ring. <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Revised Standard Version (1989)\">NRSV</abbr> just converts it to the shekel weight by saying “a gold nose-ring weighing a half shekel.” The <em>beqa‘</em> equals 10 gerahs.</h2>\n</div>",
